cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.DC

This paper deals with the privacy risks associated with offloading deep neural network computations to the cloud. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses techniques for obfuscating data, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Hence, it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper deals with image classification, which falls under the category of computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another likely category. The paper also discusses the use of resource-constrained devices, which could fall under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the use of cloud computing, which could fall under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
